essly and selflessly gave toward the revolution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aalternative to traditional historical narratives.  adaughters.  adiary.  aelites.  afamily histories.  afamily letters.  afemale historical figure.  aforgetting the experience of ordinary individuals.  agovernment and governing.  ahistorical documents.  ahistorical issues.  alife journey.  amanuscripts.  amemoir.  amothers.  apersonal letters.  asocial history.  aupper class vs lower class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771991964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771991964/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles